<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1074,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1074,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[324,372,1075,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">type</typeStatus>
and only species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 2011" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="2011" box="[601,890,1074,1099]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Pleurocalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[601,752,1074,1099]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Pleurocalliax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[759,890,1074,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10428" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida) Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 32288 / 32288. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">Sakai, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was said to be “rather similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[1300,1348,1075,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[294,435,1110,1135]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,435,1110,1135]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1902" box="[449,652,1110,1135]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goniophthalma">
<emphasis box="[449,652,1110,1135]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. goniophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
... but differs in that in 
<taxonomicName box="[913,1163,1110,1135]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Calliactites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coecigena">
<emphasis box="[913,1163,1110,1135]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Calliactites coecigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[sic] abdominal pleuron 2 is armed with a laterally directed acute projection posteroventrally, pleura 3–4 with a laterally-directed acute projection medioventrally, and pleura 5–6 with a laterally-directed acute projection anteroventrally; whereas in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. J. Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[151,471,1218,1243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goniophthalma">
<emphasis box="[151,471,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis goniophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
abdominal pleura 2–5 are unarmed and pleuron 6 is armed with a laterally-directed acute projection anteroventrally”. The only figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock &amp; Anderson" authorityYear="1894" box="[751,1004,1254,1279]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caecigena">
<emphasis box="[751,1004,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianassa caecigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Alcock &amp; Anderson, 1896: pl. 26 fig. 2) illustrate the pleural spines. As well as the strong lateral tooth on pleuron 6, both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. J. Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[1119,1323,1290,1315]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goniophthalma">
<emphasis box="[1119,1323,1290,1315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. goniophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9452" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1904) Decapod crustaceans of the northwest coast of North America. Harriman Alaska Expeditions, 10, 1 - 210. Available from: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 15921 (accessed 26 July 2017)" type="journal article">Rathbun 1904: 156, pl. 8</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lin, Komai &amp; Chan" authorityYear="2007" box="[413,545,1326,1351]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anovalis">
<emphasis box="[413,545,1326,1351]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. anovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lin 
<emphasis box="[616,676,1326,1351]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
2007: fig. 1) possess a spine or angle on pleura 1 and 5, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,444,1362,1387]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritana">
<emphasis box="[151,444,1362,1387]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax mauritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a spine on pleura 1 and 6 (
<figureCitation box="[791,873,1362,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Callianopsis mauritana (Sakai, Türkay, Beuck&amp; FreiWald, 2015). A–E, holotype of Phaetoncalliax mauritana, F, paratypeof P.mauritana, SMF44111.A, carapacein lateral vieW; B,same in dorsalvieW;C, D, left pleopod,posterior vieW;E, same, anterior vieW; F, left and right pleopods 1 in situ, arroW points to pleuron 1 spine. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1196970/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1074,1819]" box="[199,1173,1398,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 2011" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="2011" box="[403,722,1398,1423]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Neocallianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[403,584,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Neocallianopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[591,722,1398,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10428" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida) Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 32288 / 32288. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">Sakai, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[786,928,1398,1423]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,928,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was discussed above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1074,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation box="[199,432,1434,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10886" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M., Beuck, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2015 b) A collection of the Infraorder Callianassidea (Decapoda, Pleocyemata) with one new genus and five new species from the Eastern Atlantic off Mauritania (R / V Maria S. Merian cruise MSM 16 / 3 ' PHAETON'). Marine Biodiversity, 45 (1), 113 - 133. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 014 - 0227 - 2" type="journal article">
Sakai 
<emphasis box="[274,336,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
(2015b
</bibRefCitation>
: 125) asserted that their new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[871,1041,1434,1459]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,1041,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[1205,1347,1434,1459]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1347,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that pleopod 1 is biramous (vs uniramous) and pleopod 2 has different relative lengths of appendix masculina and endopod. In addition, they listed the presence (Table 3) of a dorsal postcervical ridge on the carapace (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,321,1542,1567]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,321,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[442,583,1542,1567]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,583,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="2011" box="[637,788,1542,1567]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Pleurocalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,788,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Pleurocalliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1074,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
Study of the 
<typeStatus box="[343,441,1578,1603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
and male 
<typeStatus box="[558,654,1579,1603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[693,987,1578,1603]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritana">
<emphasis box="[693,987,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax mauritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows, that the distal article of pleopod 1 is entire (
<figureCitation box="[280,397,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Callianopsis mauritana (Sakai, Türkay, Beuck&amp; FreiWald, 2015). A–E, holotype of Phaetoncalliax mauritana, F, paratypeof P.mauritana, SMF44111.A, carapacein lateral vieW; B,same in dorsalvieW;C, D, left pleopod,posterior vieW;E, same, anterior vieW; F, left and right pleopods 1 in situ, arroW points to pleuron 1 spine. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1196970/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4C–F</figureCitation>
) and uniramous as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[650,791,1614,1639]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[650,791,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The difference in the pleopod 2 is not convincing when comparing 
<bibRefCitation box="[278,769,1650,1675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10428" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida) Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 32288 / 32288. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">
Sakai (2011: fig. 
<date box="[472,509,1650,1675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" value="1963-01">63I</date>
for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. J. Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[557,760,1650,1675]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goniophthalma">
<emphasis box="[557,760,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. goniophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[824,1041,1650,1675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10886" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M., Beuck, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2015 b) A collection of the Infraorder Callianassidea (Decapoda, Pleocyemata) with one new genus and five new species from the Eastern Atlantic off Mauritania (R / V Maria S. Merian cruise MSM 16 / 3 ' PHAETON'). Marine Biodiversity, 45 (1), 113 - 133. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 014 - 0227 - 2" type="journal article">
Sakai 
<emphasis box="[894,950,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
(2015b
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 6f for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[1168,1313,1652,1675]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritana">
<emphasis box="[1168,1313,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">P. mauritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Contrary to 
<bibRefCitation box="[180,421,1686,1711]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10886" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M., Beuck, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2015 b) A collection of the Infraorder Callianassidea (Decapoda, Pleocyemata) with one new genus and five new species from the Eastern Atlantic off Mauritania (R / V Maria S. Merian cruise MSM 16 / 3 ' PHAETON'). Marine Biodiversity, 45 (1), 113 - 133. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 014 - 0227 - 2" type="journal article">
Sakai 
<emphasis box="[249,306,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
’s (2015b)
</bibRefCitation>
statement, both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. J. Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[606,809,1686,1711]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goniophthalma">
<emphasis box="[606,809,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. goniophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lin, Komai &amp; Chan" authorityYear="2007" box="[864,992,1686,1711]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anovalis">
<emphasis box="[864,992,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">C. anovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an elevated mid-dorsal ridge near the posterior margin of the carapace as does 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[644,788,1724,1747]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritana">
<emphasis box="[644,788,1724,1747]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">P. mauritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[802,892,1722,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Callianopsis mauritana (Sakai, Türkay, Beuck&amp; FreiWald, 2015). A–E, holotype of Phaetoncalliax mauritana, F, paratypeof P.mauritana, SMF44111.A, carapacein lateral vieW; B,same in dorsalvieW;C, D, left pleopod,posterior vieW;E, same, anterior vieW; F, left and right pleopods 1 in situ, arroW points to pleuron 1 spine. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1196970/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Given the similarity between all four species in the carapace, pleonite 6, uropods, chelipeds and elsewhere, the alleged differences are insufficient to warrant generic differentiation and the genera are therefore synonymous.
</paragraph>
